{"_id":"52P0oEzuhOxEpUeL","name":"With a Sword or a Smile","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a skilled swordsman and possess fine manners, which is why the Order considers me an excellent candidate to move among High Society. I love indulging in good food and dissolute company.<h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scene you may perform a gesture of extreme precision with your weapon, such as slipping an object off someone or writing something on a surface. The person observing your skill will either be impressed or intimidated, depending on the Storyteller’s decision. You receive 1 Additional Success when you use the emotion you have aroused to your advantage.","notes":"James the Swordsman - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 4.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241682,"modifiedTime":1783973241682,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"4Er2vZHbi9F9A3q3","name":"Tick-Tock, Here Comes The Beast","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I have learned to face monsters and aberrations without being intimidated. The Beast is on my trail because, having tasted my flesh, it can no longer do without it…<h3>Gift</h3>While outdoors, you may ask the Storyteller for the Beast to come in search of your flesh. The Beast is a monstrous NPC with the following characteristics: OL Hard 7 – (4 Wounds).\n\nDescriptor (the Beast): I am a great and mighty beast. I overwhelm everything I come across on my way to snatch my prey.\n\nGift – Ravenous Madness: The Beast has an insane craving for your flesh, and will unleash its rage on anyone standing in its way. With its titanic strength, it can tear down trees and walls, and hurl a man away with a single swipe of its huge paws. The Beast is also quite stupid and will leave the Scene as soon as you are out of sight. You receive 2 Additional Successes to any Defense Check against it. If the Beast suffers the fourth Wound, it will dissolve. However, it will regenerate and can be used in the next Scene.","notes":"James the Swordsman - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 4.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241682,"modifiedTime":1783973241682,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"q9Eeoh4nUrghlYwr","name":"Find Them Forever After","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>My senses are unfailing. Nothing can escape my sense of smell and that is why the Order uses me as a guardian. I hate strong smells and loud noises because they feel like burning irons to acute senses.<h3>Gift</h3>Once you catch someone’s scent, you never forget it. During a Scene, you can spend 1 Soma to memorize the scent of a person you are interacting with. You will always recognize it and it will be easy for you to follow its traces even after some time. If you concentrate, you can hear a noise even at great distances. When someone approaches you, the Storyteller will warn you long before anyone else in the Scene would notice.","notes":"Garou the Old Wolf - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 6.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241683,"modifiedTime":1783973241683,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"TaBngn2M45QofXhV","name":"Wolf Among the Lambs","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>A true predator knows how to appear as the most helpless of lambs. I know how to disguise myself. My confidence is boundless and I often tend to underestimate danger, ready to risk anything for a tasty bite.<h3>Gift</h3>You may spend 1 Soma to assume the shape of a common human. Create a Descriptor that represents you and includes at least one of these words: Old, Helpless, Weak. In your human form you can speak and act without problems, but, as soon as you use your Dark Ego, you will immediately lose the effect of Wolf Among the Lambs. You receive 1 Additional Success when you use the Descriptor you created to deceive someone and catch them off guard.","notes":"Garou the Old Wolf - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 6.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241683,"modifiedTime":1783973241683,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"CsTSoZKm9vDjPrVu","name":"Soul Music","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>With my pipe I can play any melody and touch the hearts of living beings. Art needs time to express itself.<h3>Gift</h3>When you play your pipes you can spend 1 Soma to sing a special melody. Choose from:\n1. Imparting an emotion: Create a Descriptor that represents the emotional state you wish to convey. Everybody present will receive that Descriptor for the current Scene. You may have to make a Position Check to affect opponents.\n2. Bewitching animals: You may give simple commands to animals that hear your melody. If they show an aggressive attitude, you have to make a successful Position Check for your melody to take effect. As long as you are playing, you may ask the animals to do simple actions such as moving or following a simple command.","notes":"The Astonishing Pied Piper Without a Name - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 8.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241683,"modifiedTime":1783973241683,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"sHlC9iRDSA2fcJNO","name":"Skilled Acrobat","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a skilled acrobat and musician. My talent is unrivaled and the Order has chosen me for my ability to capture people’s attention and stimulate their emotions. When I am in the grip of artistic inspiration, I am totally divorced from reality.<h3>Gift</h3>When you sing, dance, or move with grace, you always put on a great show. As an additional action, you can spend 1 Soma and decide on one of the following effects:\n1. You can make an incredible leap, many feet high, without anyone being able to stop you.\n2. You may take an object, even if it is worn by an enemy.\n3. You can perform a minor action with a stunt, such as opening a door or flipping a switch, and then return exactly to where you started.","notes":"The Astonishing Pied Piper Without a Name - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 8.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241683,"modifiedTime":1783973241683,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"qLQKV2vzzkXVDOw5","name":"Magic","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a sorceress and my magical powers allow me to do whatever I want. I need the right amount of time to cast my spells.<h3>Gift</h3>When you want to achieve something, you may use witchcraft. Choose what you want with a sentence like: I want to fly on that old broom, or I want to look like a demon in the eyes of those fools. Your spell must be focused on an object in your possession, such as a broom to fly or a mask you can wear to look like a demon. Pay a cost from 0 to 2 Soma, decided by the Storyteller, to activate your spell for the duration of a Scene. Remember that you can’t ask for someone’s sudden death, but you can inflict Wounds with your actions through magic.","notes":"Baba yaga The Child Witch - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 10.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241683,"modifiedTime":1783973241683,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"VcPf8M39SjUm66dj","name":"Listen to my Words","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am very skilled at reading people, that is why the Order has chosen me as leader of the Hunters. I love manipulating people and I often do it merely to amuse myself.<h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scene, when you talk to someone, you can ask the Storyteller a question about them. The question must be regarding their behaviour, such as any vices or their desires they might have. You gain 1 Additional Success in any action where you exploit what you’ve discovered.","notes":"Baba yaga The Child Witch - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 10.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241683,"modifiedTime":1783973241683,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"lMzejmA0chgG9t8B","name":"I Want It!","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am determined to get what I want, and nothing will get in my way. I will kill, humiliate, or conquer anything that stands between me and my objective. As you can imagine, I sincerely hate being told no!<h3>Gift</h3>When you act with clear and direct intention to achieve an objective, you get 1 Additional Success on each Position Check. Once per Session, you can turn a Failure into an Outcome with Increment. Describe how you grit your teeth and fight to get what you want.","notes":"Regina The Thief Of Hearts - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 12.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241683,"modifiedTime":1783973241683,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"5fySaC5aRnFstgrM","name":"The Queen","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Thanks to my contacts and charisma, I always have an ace up my sleeve: followers ready to help me and allies who owe me favors. Maintaining an empire of beneficial connections requires commitment and resources.<h3>Gift</h3>During a Scene you always have a couple of trusted servants with you, ready to execute your every order. Create a Descriptor for each, which represents the skill for which you hold them in your service. Your servants will do their best to satisfy your every wish. Decide how you pay them. The Storyteller, when and if they deem it necessary, will ask you to honor their services so as not to lose the use of this Gift for the rest of the Scene. You can check this Descriptor multiple times to get XP.","notes":"Regina The Thief Of Hearts - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 12.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241683,"modifiedTime":1783973241683,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"djm8vL5cXPteEP7B","name":"Eye of the Judge","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am good at understanding, evaluating, and grasping every hidden detail, which is why the Order wanted me as a judge. I am cold, methodical, and cannot stand when plans change abruptly.<h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scene, when you meet a group of NPCs you will immediately understand who is the most and the least capable of them. Moreover, the Storyteller will also reveal to you if there are relationships such as love, hate, or fidelity between two NPCs of your choice. Receive 1 Additional Success when you use the information you have discovered to intimidate or question someone.","notes":"Babai the Judge - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 14.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241683,"modifiedTime":1783973241683,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"ceylWrWEYSJL6RwN","name":"Like a Shadow","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>My body is made of pure shadow and I can become intangible for brief moments. I hate sunlight and cannot properly focus when not surrounded by a comforting shadow.<h3>Gift</h3>You can spend 1 Soma to manipulate the shadows to your advantage, choose from:\n1. Acquire a small object, even if it is held by someone, as long as you can see it.\n2. Make an object in your immediate vicinity topple down.\n3. Stretch a shadow and manipulate its shape to make it look different.\nAdditionally, you always receive 1 Additional Success on any Defense Check you make while in a shaded area. If you get a successful Outcome, as an additional effect you can move from one shadow to another and no one can prevent it.","notes":"Babai the Judge - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 14.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241683,"modifiedTime":1783973241683,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"7zK5ruOvacHlkLRY","name":"The Woman from the Wood","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am incredibly strong. Despite my petite looks, I am tougher than the sturdiest of men. I struggle to control my strength and often end up damaging things unintentionally.<h3>Gift</h3>You receive 1 Additional Success to any Position Check that requires you to resort to your strength. If you eliminate a living being by causing a Wound, you can do it in an extremely disturbing way. Anyone who witnesses it, at the discretion of the Storyteller, will lower their Opposition Level by 1 for the next action.","notes":"The Woman from the Woods - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 16.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241683,"modifiedTime":1783973241683,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"0r5wTVecsQT5E1w2","name":"Home Sweet Home","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Sometimes I manifest strange abilities, the legacy of a past that I no longer remember. But, when I need it, the world around me shapes itself to protect and shelter me. I hate being out in the open and being the center of attention.<h3>Gift</h3>You can spend 1 Soma to draw on the strange powers of the witch you once were. When you do so, choose one of the following effects:\n1. Create a shelter for one person, perfectly camouflaged within the environment.\n2. Reshape a plant to create ladders, shields, or other simple structures.\n3. Make something disgusting/rotten edible and sweet, restoring 1 Wound to whoever eats it (except yourself).","notes":"The Woman from the Woods - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 16.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241683,"modifiedTime":1783973241683,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Y5sJ13e5zX9XfL7i","name":"Memories of an Infinite Life","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I have knowledge and wisdom drawn from centuries of existence, which I can conjure to mind when needed. I often get lost in the memories of my past glories, forgetting about the world around me.<h3>Gift</h3>You have been alive for an indefinite time and know almost everything. Once per Scene, you may ask for information about the past or a specific subject or place, which is only available to you due to your long history. The Storyteller will provide relevant and useful details. Once per Scene, you may also change the above Descriptor associated with this Gift to one that represents a skill you have conjured to your immortal mind. This new Descriptor is yours until the end of the Scene, and you receive 1 Additional Success the first time you use it for a Check.","notes":"TheImmortal - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 18.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241684,"modifiedTime":1783973241684,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"bcT1QEF8ADjLmIKd","name":"The Servant","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>The Order uses my powers for their own purposes and I have had to become skilled at understanding and supporting the needs of my allies as a result. Although I hate to admit it, over time I have begun to take some pleasure in doing good deeds.<h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scene, as an additional action, you can grant 1 Additional Success to an ally’s action if you can narratively support them. You can also always spend your Soma to pay the activation cost of your allies’ Gifts.","notes":"TheImmortal - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 18.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241684,"modifiedTime":1783973241684,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"5Agi2C10c5gkIBjj","name":"Sea Magic","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a sea witch, and as such, I have the power to shape water and move it at will. I hate enclosed places, cut off from the presence of my beloved sea.<h3>Gift</h3>You can unleash your witch powers and control seawater, manipulating it as if it were solid. You can use it as a weapon or as an object to support your actions, giving it the consistency of a whip that can reach up to thirty feet. When you act, you can take a second supporting action, such as picking up something, moving someone you want to defend, or hindering an enemy’s movement thanks to the water you manipulate. You can also use this Gift with fresh water, but you will need to spend 1 Soma to do so.","notes":"Marina the Sea Explorer - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 20.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241684,"modifiedTime":1783973241684,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"bG8JfbF5U5HFUoPH","name":"Mutable Appearance","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Nobody knows my true form, which I hide under an appearance of eternal youth. I can change shape to some extent, while still remaining in human form. I am hopelessly attracted to all forms of beauty and I often get lost in contemplating it.<h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scene you can change your appearance. Create a Descriptor that represents your new appearance. Nobody can pierce your deception, except through magical means or Gifts that allow one to discover the truth. In addition, you may spend 1 Soma to take the specific appearance of a person you have already met, mimicking their voice and manners as well. You can keep your new appearance until the Scene is over.","notes":"Marina the Sea Explorer - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 20.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241684,"modifiedTime":1783973241684,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"gr7MuS6t2mSRWdmP","name":"Exorcist","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a skilled exorcist. I know how to identify and fight evil through prayer and the sacred arts. Despite what I am, I hate holy places and manifestations of faith and religion, as they cause the demon inside me to stir.<h3>Gift</h3>When you face a clearly supernatural being, you gain 1 Additional Success on all Checks. You can also invoke sacred rites and prayers to disturb the evil you face. If a subject, artifact, or supernatural manifestation uses a Gift that you know of or have already seen in action, you can spend 1 Soma to prevent its use. Each time you activate this Gift, roll 1 die. If you roll a 5 or a 6, you gain 1 Devil Token.","notes":"Niklaus von Krampus - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 22.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241684,"modifiedTime":1783973241684,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"FPGE8GTd7Tisi087","name":"The Inner Demon","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am good at understanding people and helping them. Now, thanks to the demon that dwells in me, I can even perceive the dark side of people. Every so often, however, the demon takes over, making me behave strangely in front of ordinary people.<h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scene, you can release the inner demon, whether that’d be yours or someone else’s. In your case, create a Descriptor that represents an emotion that includes the word Anger, Envy, or Wickedness. You receive 2 Additional Successes the first time you use this Descriptor for a Position Check. If you unleash someone else’s inner demon, the Storyteller will create a Descriptor for them that showcases their hidden, dark side. When using this Gift on particularly powerful individuals, the Storyteller may request a Position Check from you to succeed. Each time you use this Gift, you receive 1 Devil Token.","notes":"Niklaus von Krampus - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 22.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241684,"modifiedTime":1783973241684,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"ySKDCScZaDUbJ6Hl","name":"The Dragon Slayer","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I have dedicated my life to slaying monsters and aberrations, honing my body and my skill for that purpose. My strict discipline makes me rarely inclined to forgive the mistakes of others.<h3>Gift</h3>You’re skilled at slaying monsters and demonic creatures in the name of faith. You start each Scenario with 1 Fervor Token. When facing an enemy that is obviously monstrous, if you get a successful Outcome on a Position Check, you can spend 1 Fervor Token to inflict 1 additional Wound. When such an enemy attempts to overwhelm you using one of their Gifts, you can spend 1 Fervor Token to receive 2 Additional Successes to your Defense Check. When you suffer 1 Wound, you receive 1 Fervor Token.","notes":"George the Holy Dragon Slayer - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 24.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241684,"modifiedTime":1783973241684,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"IWSjQ2sCs0RN8Hkt","name":"Agent of the Papacy","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I have vowed to eradicate all evil from this world and nothing can escape my inquisitive gaze. I hate all secrets, for I know that the seed of evil may grow within anyone.<h3>Gift</h3>When you speak to a crowd you can infuse their hearts with the light of faith. Spend 1 Fervor Token and you can create a Descriptor that represents a feeling of faith, anger, and a desire for justice against evil. Alternatively, create a Descriptor that represents trust and submission in such faith. The crowd will act accordingly for the rest of the Scene, but particularly powerful NPCs may be immune to your words. Receive 1 Additional Success on any Check you make using the sentiment you inspired. When you publicly expose evil, you receive 1 Fervor Token.","notes":"George the Holy Dragon Slayer - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 24.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241684,"modifiedTime":1783973241684,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"cokRwKE7Y5YGNw8F","name":"Guardian Disciple","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a skilled guardian. My body is strong and hardened, my senses sharp and alert. Years of captivity have made me submissive, and I struggle not to follow every order I am given.<h3>Gift</h3>You can intercept a danger before it overwhelms your ally. You may spend 1 Soma to get between an ally and a danger by standing in their place. Receive 1 Additional Success to any Defense Check you have to perform doing so. Once per Scenario, you can ignore 1 Wound you suffer.","notes":"Sun Wukong the Amazing Monkey - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 26.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241684,"modifiedTime":1783973241684,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"UP9F1Xlj7PiUZNAr","name":"Monkey King","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am stronger and faster than any human and I am a highly skilled fighter. I don’t shy away from a challenge because I always believe I can win.<h3>Gift</h3>You are able to perform athletic feats unthinkable to a mere mortal. You may spend 1 Soma and choose an effect:\n1. You can jump incredibly far, up to thirty feet. You can bring another person with you by carrying them on your shoulders. You also ignore any damage related to a fall.\n2. Use your tail to manipulate an object and perform an additional action.\n3. Ignore any physical impediments to movement by using your impressive skills.","notes":"Sun Wukong the Amazing Monkey - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 26.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241684,"modifiedTime":1783973241684,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"ZxDYlv4D0HVw1mz3","name":"Problem Solver","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>My specialty is problem solving and I have a talent for analyzing every situation, allowing me to find resources and discover clues. Managing danger requires calm and concentration, and so I hate acting precipitously.<h3>Gift</h3>If you’ve seen it once, you can do it yourself even better. You may spend 1 Soma to replicate the effect of a Gift from a Hunter or NPC you witnessed during the Scenario. Particular Gifts may still be off limits or only yield a part of their effect at the Storyteller’s discretion. You cannot replicate more than one Gift at a time. Once per Scene, you may ask the Storyteller to reveal to you a Gift of an NPC that you had time to study.","notes":"Verdoux Bluebeard - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 28.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241684,"modifiedTime":1783973241684,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Idxe24jCjc2wMGG5","name":"The Key to Each Door","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am an educated man who has studied the arts and sciences. I use this knowledge to uncover truths and reveal mysteries. I hate secrets, but only when I don’t know them.<h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scene, you can use one of the magic keys you own. Choose an effect:\n1. Open a closed door, no matter how many locks or defenses it has.\n2. If a subject touches your key, discover the strongest feeling they are experiencing.\n3. Close and lock a door so that no conventional methods will be able to open it.\n4. If you put your key in the mouth of a dead person you will see some of their memories. The Storyteller will describe them to you, focusing on your areas of interest.","notes":"Verdoux Bluebeard - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 28.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241684,"modifiedTime":1783973241684,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"b9AUvgy9zw1MjG0J","name":"Otherworldly Charm","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a highly skilled artist. Music, dance, and painting hold no mysteries for me. My otherworldly charm captivates ordinary people, always drawing attention to me.<h3>Gift</h3>When you perform or flaunt your talents, all eyes will be on you. Receive 1 Additional Success for each Position Check you make to attract attention or charm someone. If you get an Outcome with an Increment, you may declare that a subject who has seen you has fallen in love with you. The Storyteller will create a specific Agenda for them that leads them to seek your attention.","notes":"Yukie Onn the Traveling Artist - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 30.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241684,"modifiedTime":1783973241684,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"3AsfE7yutWSbrZpo","name":"Blood-Hot","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I cannot feel pain and my frail appearance hides surprising physical abilities. Blood is the only thing that can warm me and its smell alone makes me shiver.<h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scene, you can consume a person’s blood when inflicting 1 non-fatal Wound. You recover 1 Wound, 1 Soma and receive some information about your victim such as a memory, an emotion or their heart’s desire. When you drink blood roll a die: if you roll a 1, you lose control and you will kill your victim by draining their blood, unless someone stops you.","notes":"Yukie Onn the Traveling Artist - bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 30.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241685,"modifiedTime":1783973241685,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"LRDD8cTeQUKL4Nq9","name":"Believe in Miracles (Cunning)","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Cunning's Descriptor: I have a natural talent for telling lies, which the Order often uses to its advantage. Despite my origins, I know a great deal about many things because lying requires planning and preparation.<h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scene, you can tell everyone something that will be accepted without question until the lie is uncovered. The deception becomes obvious at the end of the Scene or once exposed. Gain +1 Success on any Check where you exploit the lie.","notes":"Cunning Machiavelli the Fox and Sly Bischeri the Cat - bt-cb-foxcat-sheet-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 2.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241685,"modifiedTime":1783973241685,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"CidAb29Mxv5o6kdI","name":"Rogue (Sly)","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Sly's Descriptor: A life on the road has taught me to be a skilled thief. Everyone for themselves is my motto.<h3>Gift</h3>By pretending to be weak during a Scene, NPCs will overlook you unless you acted against them. By spending 1 Soma, you can flee any Scene involving a crowd.","notes":"Cunning Machiavelli the Fox and Sly Bischeri the Cat - bt-cb-foxcat-sheet-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 2.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241685,"modifiedTime":1783973241685,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"D9yDioGcrt7LHFkF","name":"Partner in Crime (Common)","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Common Descriptor: I will stop at nothing to get what I want, and it only takes me a few seconds to evaluate what is happening and find the right way to take advantage of it. I hate acting alone because there's no one to take the blame.<h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scene, when an ally acts with your support, they receive +1 Additional Success. Additionally, if an ally achieves an Outcome with an Increment, you may immediately take an extra action.","notes":"Cunning Machiavelli the Fox and Sly Bischeri the Cat - bt-cb-foxcat-sheet-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 2.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241685,"modifiedTime":1783973241685,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"P11cWtTr3vslnSO2","name":"Physician","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a skilled physician and psychiatrist, and \ndiagnosing illnesses is simple. My work has made me \nparticularly cold and detached.<h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scenario, when you take the \ntime to treat an injury, you may heal 1 Wound suffered \nby one of your patients, also bringing them back from \napparent death or unconsciousness. Y ou may spend 1 \nSoma to reassure and calm someone who is frightened or \nexperiencing any negative feeling. If you do, you receive \n1 Additional Success to any Check involving interactions \nwith that patient for the remaining of the Scenario.","notes":"Alice of Other Worlds - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 2.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241685,"modifiedTime":1783973241685,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"IIu1icqNI9MEyGZE","name":"Cheshire the Lynx","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Cheshire, my faithful trained lynx, is the most \ntrustworthy of companions – a shadow keeping \nme safe from threats. Cheshire’s attachment is an \nobsession and she may even threaten those who don’t \nwant to hurt me.<h3>Gift</h3>Cheshire is an NPC fully \nunder your control, with the following profile:\nOL Medium 5 – (2 Wounds) \nDescriptor: I am a big, short-tempered wild lynx and I only \nlive to serve Alice.\nGift - Two Souls: Y ou share your soul with Cheshire, and \nyou can see and feel through her senses. Y ou can spend \n1 Soma to make Cheshire immaterial for an action and \nallow her to cross any obstacle.","notes":"Alice of Other Worlds - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 2.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241685,"modifiedTime":1783973241685,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"LdYhP9N9slD50po2","name":"The Beast","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Dionysus follows me and protects me like a faithful beast, \nand responds to all my commands. As useful as this is, I feel \ndisgusted every time he comes near me.<h3>Gift</h3>Dionysus is an NPC fully under your control, \nwith the following profile:\nOL Medium 5 – (Wounds: as Bella’s current value) \nDescriptor: I am a powerful and feral beastman. Only Bella’s scent \nkeeps me under control.\nGift - Monstrous: If he intends to kill someone, Dionysus may \nact twice in each Exchange. Once per Scene, Dionysus can break \nor lift even a large object with extreme ease. \nDuring Scenes, you decide how Dionysus acts. Any Wound one \nof you suffers also applies to the other. When Dionysus is within \na few steps, you receive 1 Penalty to each Check due to the strong \ndisgust you feel for him.","notes":"Beauty and her Beast - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 4.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241685,"modifiedTime":1783973241685,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"9xMPxcweQMCXV6QM","name":"The Beauty","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am charismatic and affable. My innate air of superiority \nfascinates simple people. I love having all my eyes on me.<h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scene, when you meet a new subject, \nyou may spend 1 Soma and declare that you have met them in the \npast and that you made some kind of deal with them. Create, in \nagreement with the Storyteller, an Agenda for them representing \nthe deal. If you take the time to talk to someone, the Storyteller \nmust reveal a clue about their current Agenda or a drawback of \none of their Descriptors. When someone shows a strong interest \nin you, Dionysus, if present, loses the use of the Monstrous Gift \nbecause of the strong jealousy and shame he feels for himself.","notes":"Beauty and her Beast - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 4.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241685,"modifiedTime":1783973241685,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"CLo7M3IyIdCCQKxK","name":"Mutant","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>My touch is capable of mutating other beings with devastating \nresults. The flesh deforms before it explodes. When I am in the \ngrip of strong emotions, I lose control of my power and I am \nafraid to touch the people I care about.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou start the Scenario with 3 Mutation Tokens. \nY ou may spend 1 Mutation Token to modify a part of your body, \nsuch as turning your arms into wings or your skin into a thick \ncarapace. Create a Descriptor that represents the mutation. Y ou \ngain 1 Additional Success whenever you take advantage of your \nmutation. Whenever you change shape, the Storyteller can decide \nthat the hormone emitted by your body bewilders the mind of an \nNPC nearby, creating a specific Agenda for them that leads them \nto seek you in some way. Y our mutations remain until the end of \nthe Scene. Once per Scenario, the Storyteller can declare that this \nGift is activated without you realizing it and give you 1 Mutation \nToken.","notes":"Bloodwhite - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 6.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241685,"modifiedTime":1783973241685,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"oEwfnFacOiKTb9DE","name":"Mutagenic Touch","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a good girl and believe in the power of love and justice. My \npure gaze reaches the hearts of the people close to me. I try to \navoid those that look at me with disgust, believing me to be a \nmonster.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou can inflict 1 Wound to a living \nbeing with the touch of your hand. If you kill the target this way, \nit will explode in a gruesome way, scaring everyone present. The \nmost impressionable NPCs, at the Storyteller’s discretion, will \nthen try to avoid any confrontation with you. When you achieve \nan Outcome with an Increment with your touch and kill someone, \nyour body assimilates part of the exploded flesh, and you may \nrecover 1 Mutation Token or 1 Soma.","notes":"Bloodwhite - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 6.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241685,"modifiedTime":1783973241685,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"glgz3sVj6UB49xqi","name":"Lies","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I want to prove that I am a good boy, and that is why I strive \nto perform every task that is assigned to me. I naively tend to \ntrust adults blindly, even if I just met them.<h3>Gift</h3>When you tell a lie, you can temporarily make it a \nreality. Create a Descriptor that represents your lie and concerns \nsomething about you that you pride yourself on, such as: I have the \nstrength of five men, or I can fly through the air. The Descriptor \nremains throughout the Scene, and you gain 1 Additional Success \nthe first time you use it for an action. Each time you make use of this \nGift you receive 1 Lie Token. Y our nose will grow in proportion \nto the amount of Lie Tokens you have. During the Scenario the \nStoryteller can spend 1 Lie Token to give you 1 Penalty on a Check, \ndescribing how your clumsy puppet body prevents you from \nperforming at your best. With every Lie Token spent, your nose \nshrinks closer back to normal.","notes":"Wound. Carlo the LivingPuppet - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 8.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241685,"modifiedTime":1783973241685,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"j4m0fG8e8PXi5PJw","name":"Always in the Middle of Trouble","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scene, \nwhen you face a danger or problem arising from a previous choice \nyou have made, you recover 1 Soma and get 2 XP . When you do \nwhat an NPC asks and trust them without asking questions, you \ncan discard 1 Lie Token.","notes":"Wound. Carlo the LivingPuppet - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 8.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241685,"modifiedTime":1783973241685,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"RAAw6TxxHEG38Zl2","name":"Time Watches","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a good toymaker and the small automata I build can \nperform the most varied tasks. All my creations have a touch \nof my madness and sometimes they don’t work exactly as they \nshould.<h3>Gift</h3>When you want to use time to your \nadvantage, you can twist the stem on one of your watches and choose \nfrom the following. \n1. Slow the World Down: Receive 1 Additional Success to your \nnext Position Check.\n2. Speed up the Hatter: Y ou can act immediately (unless you \nhave already done so during the Exchange) by interrupting anyone’s \naction, regardless of what else might be happening in the narrative. \nWhen you use your watches, you gain 1 Time Token. During the \nScenario, the Storyteller can spend 1 Time Token to freeze you a few \nseconds in time and give you 2 Penalties to a Defense Check. If you \ntake an Interlude and drink some good tea, you can discard all the \nTime Tokens you have accumulated.","notes":"Hatta Carter - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 10.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241685,"modifiedTime":1783973241685,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"fN5qD1XEpUoNl8aN","name":"Playmates","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Gift</h3>Y ou own three automated dolls, The Little \nHatter, The Hare, and The Dormouse. Each automaton can perform \nsmall tasks, such as picking up and carrying items or delivering a \nmessage. Each doll has a special ability.\nThe Little Hatter can explode, inflicting 1 Wound to everyone \nwithin ten feet of it. \nThe Hare can always find a way, even through narrow places or \nclosed doors. \nThe Dormouse can fall asleep and deactivate to discard 1 Time \nToken. \nDuring Interludes, repair all automata.","notes":"Hatta Carter - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 10.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241685,"modifiedTime":1783973241685,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"fKZVXHaWGmwaDlyQ","name":"Ordog the Trusty Horse","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a tenacious defender and in my previous life, I always \nstood my ground, never retreating. The memory of my loved \nones makes me melancholic and I cannot forgive those who \nhurt families.<h3>Gift</h3>Ordog is a strange horseshaped entity. He can speak and is uncannily smart, but he is very \nsarcastic and capricious. Ordog will always know how to find you \nand will overcome all obstacles to reach you. When you ask for his \nhelp, Ordog will manifest his magical power and the Storyteller \nwill create a Descriptor that will allow him to do incredible things, \nsuch as fly or pass through the walls. The Storyteller has full \ncontrol of Ordog’s will and whims, so expect to have to promise \nhim something or convince him of your reasons.","notes":"The Knight with a Hundred Heads - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 12.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241685,"modifiedTime":1783973241685,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"PBpUegRzyJ4y9DDY","name":"The Bridge","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Gift</h3>When you protect a place or honor an oath \nyou have taken, nothing can overwhelm you. Once per Scene, you \nmay declare an oath in which you swear to defend something and \ngain 3 Oath Tokens. As long as you act to fulfill your oath, you can \nspend 1 Token to:\n1. Resist being separated from what you are defending.\n2. Gain 1 Additional Success for a Defense Check.\n3. Inflict 1 additional Wound to an enemy, but only if this allows \nyou to eliminate them. If you do, you must decapitate them. \nIf you break your oath, the magic that animates you weakens and \nthe Storyteller gains 1 Sleep Token that they can spend at any time \nto have you automatically fail a Check.\nThe Knight with \na Hundred\nHeads","notes":"The Knight with a Hundred Heads - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 12.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241685,"modifiedTime":1783973241685,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"GbvSeb7JD1pIJTdH","name":"The Red Hood","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>When I am calm, I still look like a small and helpless child \nand, thanks to this, adults tend to underestimate me. I struggle to \nbehave like a normal child, but I can’t keep my wolfish side leashed \nforever.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou can spend 1 Soma to look exactly like \na common child. Create a Descriptor that contains one of the words \nPretty, Small, or Sweet. As long as you maintain your disguise, no \nadult will notice you or consider you a potential danger. Receive 2 \nAdditional Successes to the first action you take when you decide to \ndrop your disguise and reveal who you are.","notes":"Iskra the Young Wolf - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 14.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241686,"modifiedTime":1783973241686,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"djuGk4WAtWtzd8ek","name":"Pack","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I perform my best when I’m cooperating with my hunting \ncompanions. I quickly learn the strengths and weaknesses of the \npack. I follow every order of anyone I consider more important \nthan me within the pack, without hesitation or remorse.<h3>Gift</h3>When you coordinate and act with one or more of your \nteammates against a common threat, you both get 1 Additional Success \nfor your Position Check. At the end of the Scene, if you have resolved \na significant issue thanks to the collaboration with your companions, \nyou recover 1 Soma.\nIwas abandoned by my mother in a large forest and survived by joining a pack of werewolves. After \na year of honing my predatory skills, I tracked down the woman I once called “Mother” and sank \nmy fangs into her throat. My pack was dismantled by a group of Hunters and the Order captured me.","notes":"Iskra the Young Wolf - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 14.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241686,"modifiedTime":1783973241686,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"2BMtdZUKEKEiEwKD","name":"Gang","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>We are a gang and we use numerical superiority \nto overcome our human limitations. Our faces \nare always covered by a pig’s head mask, \nintimidating ordinary people.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou can act as three independent \ncharacters using all the same Descriptors, Gifts and \nSoma. Each gang member has 1 single Wound, for a \ntotal of 3. Each of you is skilled at something.\nThe eldest gains 1 Additional Success in actions \ninvolving repairing or tampering with the \nenvironment. \nThe middle brother gains 1 Additional Success in \nactions to construct or tamper with objects.\nThe youngest gains 1 Additional Success in actions \nnot related to any kind of obligation or duty towards \nthe gang or the current mission.","notes":"The Gang of three Pigs - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 16.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241686,"modifiedTime":1783973241686,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"sDqem0qYlbID5sgX","name":"Eating the Divine","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Thanks to the flesh of the God Under the Mine, \nour body is able to regenerate. We do not fear \npain or disease. Preserving the God’s meat is an \nobsession for us, and is more important than \nanything else.<h3>Gift</h3>By eating the flesh, \nyou can regenerate your bodies and even return \nfrom death. At the end of each Scene, each member \nrecovers their Wound as long as at least one of the \nBrothers is still alive to activate the power of this Gift. \nOnce per Scenario, one of you can spend 1 Soma to \nheal immediately from 1 Wound and come back to \nlife instantly.","notes":"The Gang of three Pigs - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 16.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241686,"modifiedTime":1783973241686,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Bgq9PAgX6WXmOGaB","name":"Weaver of Destiny","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a skilled illusionist. Thanks to my power, I can conjure \ntricks of light and mirages. I am hopelessly attracted to mirrors \nand sleights of hand.<h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scene, you can give a goal \nto an ally, such as Defeat that enemy or Retrieve that item. As \nlong as your ally acts to fulfill the destiny you have indicated to \nthem, they get 1 Additional Success to all their actions. However, \nif at the end of the Scene you have not achieved your goal, you will \nboth suffer 1 Wound due to the magical backlash of destiny. When \nfaced with one or more choices, you can spend 1 Soma and ask the \nUniverse to help you decide. Choose a Keyword such as enemy, \ndanger, or something else and the Storyteller will tell you which \nof the possibilities in front of you is the most related to the word \nyou have chosen.","notes":"Morgana of the Lake - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 18.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241686,"modifiedTime":1783973241686,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"uscEV60Q6LCLaRpb","name":"Illusion","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Gift</h3>Y ou may spend 1 Soma to create up to three \nillusions and move them as you like. Create a Descriptor that \nrepresents your illusions. Every illusion is a distortion of the \nvisual field. Y ou may make them more believable by adding 1 \nelement, choosing from between sound, smell, or tactility. Y our \nillusions are realistic, but they will be exposed if closely examined. \nAlternatively, you may spend 1 Soma to create three illusory \ncopies of yourself to confuse watchers. Y ou gain 3 Additional \nSuccesses for the first Defense Check you make. Y ou then subtract \n1 Additional Success (down to zero) for each additional Defense \nCheck you must take.","notes":"Morgana of the Lake - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 18.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241686,"modifiedTime":1783973241686,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"dGfyvxPIFDwP7w5w","name":"The Silver Shoes","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I trained to be an efficient fighter and assassin, taking \nadvantage of the magical shoes I took from my first \nvictim. The disease that afflicts me disfigures my face and I \nam ashamed of my condition.<h3>Gift</h3>When you move, you can teleport \nfor short distances, and this allows you to automatically elude \nany attempt to impede or prevent your movements. Y ou need to \nsee where you intend to reappear. If you’re holding someone’s \nhand, you can spend 1 Soma to bring them with you. Once \nduring the Scenario, you may make a longer trip, even of \nseveral miles, but only to a place that you have seen at least once \nbefore.","notes":"OZena the Suffering - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 20.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241686,"modifiedTime":1783973241686,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"5B1R6OuRckIIYgE9","name":"Experience of a Dark Journey","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I have been leading a band of followers for a long time and I \nknow how a leader should behave. I’m good at imposing my \nwill on others. Even though I am often offered loyalty, being \na stranger far from my home in time and space makes it \ndifficult to trust others.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou have \naccomplished many missions with strange companions and \nhave learned something from each of them. Y ou can invoke \neach of these effects once per Scenario.\n1. Tough as Tin: Ignore 1 Wound you should suffer from \nphysical damage. \n2. The Bravery of a Lion: Y ou gain 2 Additional Successes \nwhen you throw yourself against a great danger without caring \nabout the consequences.\n3. The Brain of a Genius Scarecrow: The Storyteller \nwill provide you with useful information about a place, \npersonality, or event you are dealing with. The information you \ngain is always useful to what you’re doing.\nI am a young American girl from 1939. Because of a magic tornado, I crashed into Broken Europe with a \nstrange doctor named Norman Henkle. I am suffering from a rare form of OZena, which disfigures my face \nand has blighted my life ever since I was a child. Dr. Henkle deceived me with the promise of a cure and a way \nback to my time, asking me to become a witch hunter. I committed crimes, even murders, until the Order put \nan end to my madness. I was forgiven and found in the Order a new home that I don’t want to run away from.","notes":"OZena the Suffering - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 20.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241686,"modifiedTime":1783973241686,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"PID4MKGfJst4dW4P","name":"The Tale","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I know over a thousand stories and from each one I draw \na lesson with which to face dangers. I’ d do anything to \nlearn a new story.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou start each Scenario with 3 Story Tokens. \nOnce per Scene, you may tell a short story. If you do, spend \n1 Story Token and declare a Keyword that appears in your \nnarrative, then mark it down on your Sheet. During the \nScenario, if a Keyword you have marked is introduced during \na Scene by the Storyteller (for example, the Keyword is Soldier \nand you come across Soldiers), erase the word to get 1 XP and \n2 Additional Successes for either your next action or that of \none of your allies. When you learn an interesting new story, \nyou receive 1 Story Token.","notes":"Sherazade the Weaver of Tales - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 22.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241686,"modifiedTime":1783973241686,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"JrHlBH3gHJaOd8p6","name":"Words Like Honey","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I know the delicate art of flattery and I know how to best \ncompliment others to make them feel good. I will not \ntolerate those who use violence.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou can speak beautiful words \nto bring out a memory, an emotion, or a fear. Spend 1 Story \nToken and choose one Keyword. Each NPC or Hunter who \nhas listened to you and is connected to the Keyword will \nbe overwhelmed by their emotions and will have to create \na relevant Descriptor and keep it throughout the Scene. \nParticularly powerful subjects and Hunters who oppose your \npower may require a Position Check. Y our allies receive 1 \nAdditional Success in the first action they take when using \nany Descriptor created by this Gift.\nI am the greatest storyteller that has ever lived, having learned my skills after serving a \nwealthy sultan for many years. I can’t remember why I left, but I suddenly found myself in \nEurope, where I used my skills against the Order and the Hunters. After my defeat, I was \nforgiven, for it was clear to my jailers that a dark force had clouded my mind. I serve the Order \nto regain my freedom, but also to find the one who corrupted my heart, forcing me to do harm.","notes":"Sherazade the Weaver of Tales - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 22.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241686,"modifiedTime":1783973241686,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"ptLtINUUnpj0mo5s","name":"The Cloak","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>My body floats, carried by my power, ignoring obstacles of all \nkinds. I can use my very long hair as if it were my hands. I \ntravel in a heavy nun’s habit and wear a mask to hide my true \ncondition from the world.<h3>Gift</h3>Y our large nun’s cloak floats to defend you from \nthe world and contains many small items that you can manipulate. \nThanks to this Gift you are able to float and hover in the air, but \nalways at a speed equal to the pace of a human. Once per Scene, \nyou may:\n1. Hide an object inside your cloak, hiding it from everyone (even \nwhen searching through magic).\n2. Extract from your cloak an object that you need. It can be rare \nand peculiar, but not magic or unique.","notes":"Talia the Sleeper - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 24.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241686,"modifiedTime":1783973241686,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"yZV6K1MKZhGCezhd","name":"In the Dream","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I can communicate with those who are asleep or \nunderstand their desires and fears through dreams. I hate \nit when there are too many people around. The buzz of their \nlives reminds me of what I can’t have.<h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scene, you can freely \ncommunicate with a subject who is unconscious through a \ndream. Alternatively, you may choose to spend 1 Soma to “read” \nthe dreams of a conscious subject. The Storyteller will reveal all or \npart of the subject’s Agenda to you through the narration of one \nof their dreams. Particularly powerful subjects and Hunters may \nrequire a Position Check to be able to capture their dreams.","notes":"Talia the Sleeper - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 24.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241686,"modifiedTime":1783973241686,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"gEBrYX8wJj55wuwt","name":"Light the Flame","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I have no choice but to remain in my childish \nbody for eternity. I have a sweet smile and \npeople often feel protective towards me. Animals \nperceive me for who I really am and they act up \nin my presence.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou can manipulate fire, as \nlong as there is already a flame in the environment. \nDecide whether to increase or decrease its size or \nintensity, as well as the direction it burns. Y ou can \nalso manipulate the flame to hit something within \nnine feet of it. Y ou gain 1 Additional Success to each \naction you take while manipulating fire. The first time \nyou use this Gift in a Scene, the Storyteller may decide \nthat your action will spread the flames in some way.","notes":"Yvonne of the Dark - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 26.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241686,"modifiedTime":1783973241686,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"EViGV9h7NYGqbUBJ","name":"Innocent Smile","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Gift</h3>When you talk to someone, \nyou can spend 1 Soma to provoke their sympathy (the \nStoryteller will evaluate whether or not the subject is \nsensitive to your influence) to create an Agenda in \nwhich the target feels somehow responsible for you. \nDuring a Scene, if the location is crowded, you can \nact or move without anyone noticing.","notes":"Yvonne of the Dark - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 26.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241686,"modifiedTime":1783973241686,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"SRgoj9egHxYoN08A","name":"Snow Sorceress","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a novice a powerful sorceress with limited power total control \nover cold and snow. My magic can come with dangerous, unintended \nconsequences cause small unwanted effects.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou can use magic to create and manipulate the \ncold. Describe the effects of a spell that has one of the following Keywords \nas a condition: Ice, Snow, or Frost. Y ou could, for example, Create an Ice \nBridge to cross a crevasse or Freeze an Enemy to immobilize it. Pay a cost \nof 1 to 3 Soma, decided by the Storyteller, to activate the spell. The effects \nyou describe last until the end of the Scene. The Soma cost is increased by \n1 when environmental conditions are not compatible with cold. Y ou can \ndecide to lower the cost of the spell by 1 Soma, but this will cause a minor \nmagical accident on par with an Outcome with a Cost.","notes":"Miss Snow and Lady Storm - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 2.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241686,"modifiedTime":1783973241686,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"jwLtB80MCSCVx4ph","name":"Winter’s Kiss","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am good at understanding dominating people. I have a unique \nability to comprehend their desires. I tend to distrust even close allies \ntrust those I don’t know.<h3>Gift</h3>In you lies the power of winter. When you give \nsomeone a chaste kiss, you can choose one of the following effects:\n1. Erase one of their memories. It must be the memory of an event in the \nScene in which you use this effect. Particularly capable Hunters and \nNPCs may require a Position Check for the effect to succeed.\n2. Make the subject immune to cold throughout the rest of the Scene. \nThis will prevent them from suffering frost Wounds and allow them to \nignore the effects of Lady Storm’s snowstorm.\n3. Make an object extremely fragile.","notes":"Miss Snow and Lady Storm - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 2.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241686,"modifiedTime":1783973241686,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"IU3qpj84pEEFNg89","name":"Examine the Evidence","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>My reputation precedes me, and my word is held in the highest \nregard by anyone with an ounce of honesty. I detest criminals and \nthose who act to harm the innocent. Big or small, a crime is still \na crime.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou can use each of the following effects \nonce per Scene: \n1. For the Record: Y ou can make a note of something a subject has said; \nyou will never forget it. Write it down because you can use it when you \nactivate your Dark Ego. By spending 1 Soma, the Storyteller will reveal a \nweakness of the subject whose words you have memorized.\n2. Consult the Laws: The Storyteller will reveal to you the customs and \nrules of a social group or place you are in. By spending 1 Soma, you \ncan create a loophole, known only to you, to the rules that have been \nrevealed.\n3. The Decisive Proof: When you examine an object, the Storyteller \nwill reveal a quality or feature that few people may notice. By spending \n1 Soma, you will learn who was the last person to own or use what you \nare examining.","notes":"Tremoteus Rumpel - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 4.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241686,"modifiedTime":1783973241686,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"AWOtU7FX4aphctj0","name":"Your Honor","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a keen disputant and have an uncanny ability to detect \ndeception. I need hard evidence before I’ll accuse someone of \ndishonesty.<h3>Gift</h3>If you stand in front of nobles, lawmen, or leaders in \ngeneral, you can spend 1 Soma to have them recognize your name or \nreputation. If you use your identity as a strength, you gain 1 Additional \nSuccess. If you give your word in a negotiation, you gain 1 Additional \nSuccess in a possible Position Check.","notes":"Tremoteus Rumpel - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 4.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241686,"modifiedTime":1783973241686,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"DbfMHiJ5wScJsTOO","name":"Noble Birth","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a young prince, well-versed in the etiquette of the court. I \nam a diligent student, my favorite subjects being history and \npoetry. I am not ashamed of my strange appearance and I hate to \nhide from others.<h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scene, if you are in a place where your family’s \nauthority is recognized, you can gain access to a restricted location, such \nas a dungeon or castle, or a direct audience with an authority figure. \nAs a prince, you have learned everything a future ruler needs to know. \nOnce per Scene, you gain 2 Additional Successes for an action in which \nyou can demonstrate your knowledge of history and poetry, or your skill \nwith the sword. \nI learned kindness from my mother and firmness from my father.","notes":"Prince Trollo the Innocent - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 6.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"XmlhJpGB4Y05g2uH","name":"Good Heart","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I use these qualities to uphold the good name of my family. I will \nnot allow anyone to violate the ideals of justice and courage with \nwhich I was raised.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou have the innocence and strength of a true ruler.","notes":"Prince Trollo the Innocent - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 6.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"watwrGEFul8VNoKC","name":"Lost Childhood","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I fear nothing and throw myself into any situation. The \nadrenaline of risk drives me to succeed. I get bored easily in \nsituations where there is no danger.<h3>Gift</h3>Despite your young age, you have no qualms about \ntaking action against enemies. Y ou gain 1 Additional Success in all \nactions that require the use of subterfuge. If you attack a target that is \nunaware of your presence, you inflict 1 Additional Wound.","notes":"Pietrik and the Cauldron Fae - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 8.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"7swdUYywOetZGlZx","name":"Fearless","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>The Cauldron Fae is always with me, in the form of a small \nfloating light. Her magic is still powerful, and I often summon \nher to wreak havoc or play tricks on humans.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou are immune to any fear or mind control effects that \nprevent you from acting as you wish. If you suffer 1 Wound from an \nOpponent or Threat, you may regain 1 Soma in your next action and \nmay consider a Failure as an Outcome with a Cost.","notes":"Pietrik and the Cauldron Fae - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 8.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"55PhoLrc2WHrJTA6","name":"Thousand Faces","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a skilled acrobat, I tell stories, perform magic tricks, and put \nmy audience in a good mood. I enjoy chaos and adding confusion \nto situations is a way for me to bring balance to the world.<h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scene, you can assume the identity of \nanother Hunter. Choose a Hunter’s Sheet that no one is using and use it \nfor the rest of the Scene. Y ou have access to all the Gifts and abilities on \nthe Sheet, with the exception of the Soma points and Wounds, which you \nwill keep from Loki’s Sheet. Even though you have their likeness, you are \nnot the Hunter you are impersonating, so you do not know their personal \nhistory and cannot activate the Special Scenario Gifts associated with \nthem. Any effects of the Gifts you activate while impersonating another \nHunter will end when you return to your true identity or at the end of \nthe Scene. If someone discovers who you really are, your masquerade \nends and you take 1 Wound. If you wish, you can return to your original \nappearance before the end of the Scene. If you discover a deception and \ndo nothing to expose it, you gain 1 Soma.","notes":"Loki the Deceiver - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 10.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"afGnf3qRsdTBfCJm","name":"Trickster","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a master at distorting and unraveling deception. Verbal \nand body language hold no secrets for me. I don’t like to get my \nhands dirty and would rather have someone else do it for me.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou get 2 Additional Successes if you use your skills as \nan entertainer to perform an action. This includes polite conversation, \nsleight of hand, or performing stunts. Once per Scene, if you help an \nenemy (for example as a Cost), you gain 1 Soma.","notes":"Loki the Deceiver - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 10.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"TDr3XfSGzLjUwZC8","name":"Legacy","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am able to understand the potential of young women and know \nhow to guide their steps to develop their true potential. I consider \neach of my protégés a true daughter and would give my life to \nsave them.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou can use all the resources you have accumulated from \nyour many marriages of convenience. Y ou can use each of these effects \nonce per Scenario:\n1. A Family Asset: Y ou can bring a large property into play, such as \na mansion or business. Y ou have free access to the property and its \nresources.\n2. A Family Friend: Y ou can introduce a Minor NPC who has a debt or \npartnership agreement with your family. The Storyteller will sketch the \nNPC, who will be well-disposed towards you.\n3. A Family Treasure: Y ou can bring into play a rare and valuable item \nthat you own as a family heirloom.","notes":"The Silent Mother - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 12.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"TmNZkCFMPbuQ8vLO","name":"My Beloved Daughters","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Although I appear helpless, I am a capable spy who knows how to \ndefend herself in dangerous situations. I never miss an opportunity \nto accumulate wealth and resources.<h3>Gift</h3>Two young girls you saved from an \nunfortunate fate follow you on your adventures. Y our adopted \ndaughters are two Minor NPCs with the following profiles:\nOL Medium 5 - (1 Wound)\nDecide on their names and stories, and work with the Storyteller to \ncreate a Descriptor for each of them that describes their abilities. Y our \nadopted daughters cannot have magical abilities or more than a good \neducation in their chosen discipline. Y our daughters will do their best to \nserve you at every opportunity.","notes":"The Silent Mother - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 12.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"H4uTQc0HHnvHSjaN","name":"Monk","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am an exorcist monk. My body is tempered by a lifetime of asceticism \nand fighting evil spirits. I do not tolerate blasphemy and those who use \nknowledge for personal gain.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou can spend 1 Soma to activate a piece of your Spirit Hunter \nEquipment:\n1. Pastoral Shakujo: Banging your staff on the ground can temporarily \ninterrupt the effect of a spell or curse. The duration of the interruption (set by \nthe Storyteller) can vary from a few moments to the entire Scene, depending \non the power of the spell.\n2. Hauchiwa Fan: With a fan blast, you can make a leap of up to ten meters \nforward or upward. Y ou can use this effect on an ally.\n3. Tengu-gui Mask: Y ou can wear your mask to change your facial features, taking on a physical appearance appropriate to the context. Create a \nDescriptor that represents your appearance, but remember that you cannot \nreplicate the features of a specific subject. When you activate a Gift or suffer 1 \nWound, you will revert to your original appearance. \nThe use of this Gift is limited by the possession of the corresponding \nEquipment: if you lose an item, you cannot use the relevant option until you \nrecover it. During an Interlude, you recover any missing Equipment.","notes":"Karasu Kuroi the Wandering Monk - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 14.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"bQadkOthDVaWAoQW","name":"Moral Rigor","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Prayer keeps my mind steadfast and my words are an inspiration to \nthose who have faith. I do not tolerate the concepts of faith and \ndevotion being questioned.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou demonstrate righteousness in word and deed. Y ou gain \n1 Additional Success on all Position Checks where you make a commitment \nby giving your word as a guarantee. By spending 1 Soma, you can make \nmental contact with a subject present in the Scene who must accept the link.","notes":"Karasu Kuroi the Wandering Monk - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 14.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"PTJ17IImOJCT2s4w","name":"The Team","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>We are experienced mercenaries and have seen every battlefield. We \nhate working for free and any chance to bring home some extra loot is \ngood.<h3>Gift</h3>At the beginning of each Scene, you choose the 3 members \nof the Main Team. Y ou will receive the 3 Gifts and the Special Equipment of \nthe members you have chosen. The other 4 dwarves form the Support Team. \nThe Main Team acts as a single Hunter and receives 1 Penalty to Checks for \neach team member not present in a Scene. Wounds are also cumulative for all \nmembers, and any member can act until the Team takes its last Wound. During \na Scene, you can spend 1 Soma to swap a Main Team member for a Support \nTeam member.","notes":"The 7 Hessian Mercenaries - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 16.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"MrMN1RD6UDrDLZVb","name":"On Mission","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>We are adept at getting things, information, people, or anything you \nwant - ask and we will find it. We are intolerant of authority and \nanything with a hierarchy of command.<h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scene, you can send the Support Team on a mission \nto accomplish a goal, such as capturing an NPC, discovering information, or \nanything else you deem useful. The Storyteller sets the OL of the mission just \nlike a normal Position Check. To find out what happens, you must make a \nPosition Check, where you get 1 Base Success for each Support Team Member \n(usually 4), but you cannot spend Soma to get Additional Successes. Depending \non the result:\nFailure: The objective was missed, and one of the team members is out of the \ngame for the rest of the Scenario. Describe what happened in the words of the \nreturning teammates. If the story makes at least one other Player laugh, you will \nrecover 1 Soma.\nOutcome with a Cost: The goal was completed, but there were problems. The \nStoryteller describes how it went and suggests a complication.\nStandard Outcome: Goal completed, no problems.","notes":"The 7 Hessian Mercenaries - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 16.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"6gOWYlT1IMIOyfjK","name":"Pharmaka","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I have studied alchemy with the greatest masters, and my potions can produce wondrous effects. I am so drawn to knowledge that I neglect \nmy own safety.<h3>Gift</h3>At the beginning of each Scenario, you receive 3 Pharmaka \nTokens. Spend 1 Token when someone ingests one of your potions, then pick \none of the following effects:\n1. The subject transforms into an animal of your choice for the remainder of \nthe Scene. The person retains their human intelligence. \n2. The subject is in a confused state, which lowers their OL by 1 (or 1 Penalty in the case of a Hunter) for the rest of the Scene.\n3. The subject regains vitality and gains an Additional Wound that fades at \nthe end of the Scene.\nY ou are naturally resistant to your creations, and if you want to activate an \neffect on yourself, you must spend 1 Soma in addition to a Pharmaka Token. \nParticularly powerful subjects and Hunters may require you to perform \na Position Check before they suffer the effects of your potions. During an Interlude, or if you get your hands on valuable alchemical ingredients, you can \nrecover 1 Pharmaka Token.","notes":"Circe the Alchemist - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 20.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"tYCbUnfubNs90MdZ","name":"Travel Companion","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Eurylochus is my faithful servant pig and helps me with every task. He \nhas an almost human intelligence and one look is enough to understand \nus. I love him like a brother.<h3>Gift</h3>Eurylochus is a Minor NPC with the following profile:\nOL 5 Medium - (2 Wounds) \nDescriptor: I am Circe’s faithful pig servant and would do anything for her. \nEurylochus has always been your companion in experimentation, and over the \nyears he has been imbued with the power of Pharmaka. By spending 1 Soma, \nyou can activate one of the following effects:\n1. Human Form: Eurylochus takes the form of a handsome young man with \nflowing blond hair. He cannot speak but gains all the other advantages of a \nhuman body.\n2. Size Change: Eurylochus can shrink to the size of a mouse or grow to the \nsize of an elephant. The effect lasts for the duration of the Scene.\n3. Regeneration: Eurylochus will recover all of his Wounds, which can also \nbring him back into action if he is down to zero.","notes":"Circe the Alchemist - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 20.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Z0tIcFM5Ac5fyCMh","name":"Collect Taxes","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a lawman and I am proud of my office. I have good \nleadership skills and know how to get those in charge to carry out \nan order. I like to be praised for my abilities.<h3>Gift</h3>At the end of each Scene, you receive 1 Taxes Token \nif you have discovered riches or secrets related to a location or NPC that \nyou can use to your advantage (at the Storyteller’s discretion). Y ou start \neach Scenario with 1 Taxes Token. At any time, you can spend 1 Taxes \nToken to activate one of these effects:\n1. Ask the Storyteller to reveal an NPC’s Gift or Equipment.\n2. Allow an ally to activate a Gift by replacing a special requirement or \nSoma cost.\n3. Confer 1 Additional Success to the action of an allied Hunter.","notes":"Captain William of Nottingham - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 22.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"ExI7nwk6NZDGm6Cs","name":"Lawman","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Years of working as a bounty hunter have made me adept at \nhunting down and eliminating villains. When I am one step away \nfrom my goal, I do not consider retreating.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou can spend 1 Soma to assert your authority over \nordinary people. NPCs who recognize local authority will not try to \nharm you unless you act aggressively first. Even in cases of conflict, they \nwill avoid choosing you as a target unless you are the first to threaten \nthem. Y ou gain 1 Additional Success if you try to convince or intimidate \nsomeone who recognizes authority.","notes":"Captain William of Nottingham - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 22.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Ydgpvq9x31EhbRnP","name":"Diabolical Plan","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>My misdeeds have made me a real celebrity - I have clashed with \nheroes, nobles, and religious people, and I know how to deal with \neach of them. Sometimes I like to give my enemies a small \nadvantage just to make the challenge more interesting.<h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scenario, you can do each of the \nfollowing:\n1. Find a useful item (that you had previously planted) in your location. Receive 1 Spider Web Token.\n2. Deliver a message to someone without anyone else noticing. The \nmessage will be delivered during the Scene and, if you wish, you \nwill receive a reply at the beginning of the next Scene. Receive 1 \nSpider Web Token.\n3. Introduce an allied Minor NPC of yours to the Scene, who will be \nwilling to testify on your behalf. Receive 1 Spider Web Token.","notes":"Moriarty the Gentleman Thief - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 2.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"m4vtxMn0yFOQuZzN","name":"Dark Eminence","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am as ingenious in the use of concealed weapons and low blows \nas I am in plotting crime. The memory of my lost love has changed \nme deeply, and I try to prevent crime from creating innocent \nvictims.<h3>Gift</h3>Gain 1 Additional Success on all Checks involving \ndeception or obtaining something illegally. When you arrive at a new \nlocation, the Storyteller will reveal the possible presence of criminal \norganizations and their misdeeds. If you strike a beneficial pact with \na criminal or powerful organization, you will receive 1 Spider Web \nToken.","notes":"Moriarty the Gentleman Thief - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 2.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"0YCNZ6tWlHfbJs9J","name":"Cursed Blood","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I have a certain amount of charm and I know how to put people at ease \nwith my polite manner. I feel uncomfortable in places where I have not \nbeen invited or where it is obvious that my presence is unwelcome.<h3>Gift</h3>Y our blood has incredible properties, so at the end of each \nScene, you recover 1 Wound; this can allow you to return even if you have \nno Wounds left. Self-inflict 1 Wound to draw your blood. Whoever drinks it \n(except you) can choose one of the following effects:\n1. Recover 1 Wound.\n2. Gain 1 Additional Success (increases OL by 1 in the case of an NPC) on \nall Checks for the rest of the Scene. For each Check in which this bonus \nis used, roll a die: if you roll a 5 or 6, the blood’s effect ends.","notes":"The Pale Medic - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 4.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"uBCfl8sWTWZ7evWJ","name":"Welcome to My House","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I have vampire blood in me and my strength is far superior to that of \nan ordinary human. I am extremely sensitive to sunlight and try to \navoid it as much as possible.<h3>Gift</h3>If you care for an NPC, or are able to talk to them \nin a social setting, you gain 1 Additional Success on any Position Checks you \nmake to influence them. If the Check results in a Positive Outcome, you gain \n1 Additional Success on all Checks you make against that NPC for the rest of \nthe Scenario. After your conversation, the Storyteller will reveal something \nyou didn’t know about the NPC, such as part of their Agenda or a Gift you \nhaven’t seen in action.","notes":"The Pale Medic - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 4.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"eesYU9rJGswtGPiU","name":"Incognito Agents","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>We are a harmless middle-aged couple and no one would ever consider \nus a danger. We are adept at going unnoticed. Our passion for human \nfood drives us to real binges.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou are considered a single Hunter, sharing Soma and \nWounds, and can act 2 times per Exchange. If you are separated, each of you \nwill receive 2 Penalties to any Checks you make alone. At the end of a Scene, \nyou can wipe others’ memory of your being there.","notes":"The Respectable Mr. and Mrs. Mars - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 6.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"RLwTDbHFsEgpFNKy","name":"Informants","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>We are always connected to the Mars Operations Center, and this \nallows us to have information about history and science. We are \nmorbidly attracted to any form of art because it is totally absent on our \nworld.<h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scene, you can ask for insight into an NPC, location, or \nevent that has occurred. The Storyteller will provide you with information useful \nto your objectives. Once per Scene, if you witness the unleashing of technology, \nan invention, or a magical power, you can report back to the Operations Center.","notes":"The Respectable Mr. and Mrs. Mars - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 6.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"wgQ8nLzm4ofVm5HG","name":"Behold my Genius","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a luminary in physics and medicine and know secrets that the \nbrightest academics can only dream of. I often get lost in my own \nreasoning, which I articulate aloud without realizing it.<h3>Gift</h3>By spending 1 Soma, you can use one of your \nfuturistic discoveries to generate an electric shock that inflicts 1 Wound. \nThe thunderbolt can strike up to twenty feet away and can change its \ntrajectory to avoid obstacles. Alternatively, you can spend 1 Soma to \ncharge an object with electricity, causing it to discharge when touched and \ninflicting 1 Wound. The object remains charged until the end of the Scene.","notes":"Doctor V. Frankenstein - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 8.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"c5Y2o7Euy2otPkpJ","name":"The Creature","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I always bring the Creature with me and know how to make the \nmost of its potential. There are times when the guilt of creating such \na monster brings me back to reality, and in those rare moments, I \ntry to do a good deed to atone for my sins.<h3>Gift</h3>Y our first creation is an NPC managed by the Storyteller, \nwith the following profile: \nOL Medium 5 - (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a powerful creature who feels no pain and has the strength \nof four men. My appearance is disgusting because of the many stitches that \nhold the pieces of my body together.\nAgenda: To be considered a person like any other and to find a family to take \nme in / I wish Victor to die, but as my creator, I cannot kill him with my own \nhands, and instead I try to facilitate his passing by acting indirectly.","notes":"Doctor V. Frankenstein - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 8.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"6aYw6G7l6pCyYpK3","name":"Blessing of the Defeated","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I have a talent for assessing people’s merits and flaws, so I am good at \ncoordinating the efforts of those who trust me. I have a soft spot for those \nwho fail but try hard, and though I don’t like to admit it, sometimes the \ninstinct to help losers still takes over.<h3>Gift</h3>If your ally suffers a Wound or fails a Check, \nthey will gain 1 Additional Success (or increase their OL by 1 in the case \nof an NPC) on their next action. Alternatively, once per Scenario, you can \nchoose to have them recover 2 Soma or 1 Wound, or alternatively gain 2 XP . \nIf an NPC achieves their Agenda’s goal thanks to your help, you recover 1 \nSoma and gain 1 XP . \nI have a strong influence on people and my charm cannot be ignored.","notes":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 5 - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 10.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"wyTN5lBLT62TUoYX","name":"The Lady’s Champion","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am very vain and love to waste time admiring my own image.<h3>Gift</h3>There’s always some fool who follows you around \nand proclaims themselves your Champion, until you lose all patience. The \nStoryteller creates an NPC with the following profile at the beginning of the \nScenario:\nOL Medium 5 - (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: A positive feature that identifies the identity and abilities of the \naspiring Champion. A Downside that identifies total devotion, obsession, love, \nor admiration for Vivienne of the Lake.\nAgenda: Help and protect Vivienne at all costs. Even if my lady tells me not to \nget in her way, I must do so to ensure her safety.","notes":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 5 - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 10.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"KAEzCnLp1JNHlbYZ","name":"Porziella the Faithful Flea","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I learned some magic tricks from seven bandits, all of them brothers, \nand I know about arcane arts. I am attracted to magic and want to \ngather all knowledge about it.<h3>Gift</h3>Y our trusty flea follows you like a shadow. \nPorziella is an NPC under your full control with the following profile:\nOL Medium 5 - (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a flea the size of a dog, my skin is so hard and thick that not \neven a sword can pierce it.\nGift - Loyal Flea: Porziella always recognizes blood by its taste, which allows \nher to follow a trail or recognize who it belongs to without error. Once per \nScenario, Porziella can shield Viola by taking 1 Wound in her place. If she \ndoes this, she will be out of combat until the end of the Scene. If Porziella is \nnot present, Viola can spend 1 Soma to bring her into the Scene immediately, \novercoming all obstacles and impediments.","notes":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 6 - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 12.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"xDwDg66BZsGN6ZaP","name":"The Magic of the Seven","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am courageous and stubborn. When I speak about justice and \nequality, the passion that animates me touches people’s hearts. For me, \nthe cause comes before everything and I am ready to take any action, \neven the most extreme.<h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scenario, you can use any of the \nfollowing powers, but you must have the appropriate Equipment.\n1. Mase’s Earring: It allows you to hear a speech even through a wall.\n2. Nardo’s Soap: Gives you 3 Additional Successes to free yourself from \nropes and chains, or to slip away. \n3. C ola’s Razor: Allows you to inflict 1 Additional Wound with one attack. \n4. Micco’s Staff: Plants sprout to block a passageway; the Storyteller creates a Threat that can absorb up to 3 Wounds before yielding. \n5. Petrullo’s Water: Creates a jet of water that strikes up to 30 feet but does \nno damage. \n6. Ascadeo’s Rock: It can be thrown and will fall exactly where you want it \nto fall, without causing any damage. \n7. Ceccone’s Crossbow: Grants you 2 Additional Successes when you \nshoot a dart.","notes":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 6 - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 12.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"uXKhOUMgvGntCwgE","name":"Tiny","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I have an unusual mind and remember every detail, even years \nlater. My body is puny and I hate to do strenuous work.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou know how to go unnoticed, so no one will ever pick you as \na direct target of one of their actions if there is at least one other Hunter \nin the Scene. Y ou can spend 1 Soma to leave a location without anyone \nnoticing, as long as there is at least one other Hunter to attract attention. \nY ou get 1 Additional Success on each Check where you can use your \ndiminutive stature, but you also get 1 Penalty on each Check where you \nhave to use brute force or physical strength.","notes":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 7 - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 14.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"6se5s7Uyc4YaAqnx","name":"In the Right Place at the Right Time","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I have charisma to spare and I am a smooth talker who commands \nrespect and admiration. I must always have the last word.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou don’t get confused easily.","notes":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 7 - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 14.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"XKOAnE5QD6MzPy9d","name":"Hunting Companion","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>My senses are keen and my body is hardened by the outdoors. I hate \nbig cities, hustle and bustle, and generally can’t stand people who talk \ntoo much.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou don’t open your heart easily, but occasionally \nyou find companions you can trust. At the beginning of the Scenario, you \nchoose another Hunter as your hunting companion, who will receive 1 \nAdditional Success on all Defense Checks they make while you are in close \nproximity to cover their back. Y ou will always know where your hunting \ncompanion is and can spend 1 Soma to get to where they are, ignoring all \nobstacles. Y ou never speak and cannot express yourself verbally, but your \ncompanion will always clearly understand anything you try to tell them.","notes":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 8 - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 16.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"oIdj0J7cgqVBmxzY","name":"Stalking","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am trained to kill all kinds of beasts and know how to use the \nhunting grounds to my advantage. Monsters must always be \ndestroyed, for them I see no mercy or redemption.<h3>Gift</h3>No prey can escape you, once per Scene you can find distinct \ntraces in a place or on an object. The Storyteller will reveal a useful piece of \ninformation of your choice: who left the clue, where it is, or a weakness in the \nobject. Y ou can spend 1 Soma to blend into your surroundings: as long as you \ndo not take any conspicuous actions (at the Storyteller’s discretion), Minor \nNPCs will not be able to see you, and you will get 3 Additional Successes on \nany Checks you make to go unnoticed or catch someone off guard.","notes":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 8 - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 16.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"QFq2bXu7CaYIIcUa","name":"What I Want to See","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am used to walking around completely naked, so my physique is \ntough. I hate having unnecessary things on me, except for my beloved \ncrown.<h3>Gift</h3>If you see it, you can make it real. Y ou can spend 1 \nSoma and say what object you have in front of you. For the rest of the Scene, \nyou can use it as if it were real with all the characteristics it should have. Y ou \nget 1 Additional Success for each Check if you gain a genuine advantage due \nto the fact that others cannot see the object. Y ou can only have one object \ncreated by this Gift at a time. Y ou are completely immune to any effect based \non reducing or nullifying the ability to see.","notes":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 9 - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 18.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"EMfv49SsdU4c9ypO","name":"What I Don’t Want to See","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am good with words, I know etiquette, and I know how to dazzle the \ncrowd. I cannot refrain from commenting with the utmost sincerity \non the way my interlocutors dress.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou start each Scene in the shadows, and \nas long as you are in this state, no one will notice your presence or the fact \nthat you are completely naked. As long as you do not perform actions that \nmake you the center of attention, you can continue to do whatever you want \nwithout anyone getting in the way, and you will never be singled out for \naction by a possible enemy. Subjects who base their perception on senses \nother than sight can easily detect you. When you perform a conspicuous \naction or decide to draw attention to yourself, you shift into the light. As \nlong as you are in this state, everyone will see you for what you really are. Y ou \nget 1 Additional Success on the first Check you make when you enter this \nstate. Y ou can spend 1 Soma at any time to return to the shadows.","notes":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 9 - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 18.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
